extends JDBCQueryListener

      • executeQuery

        protected static void executeQuery(MigrationNode node,
                                   JdbcConnection conn,
                                   java.lang.String queryString,
                                   java.util.List queryAttrNames,
                                   boolean bindResultsToNode)
        Execute a SQL query from a prepared statement given a query string and a list of attributes to query against. Setting bindResultsToNode allows for both READ and UPDATE queries to be executed.
        Parameters:
        node - Node from which the query will be populated with values and which will potentially have additional attributes stored
        conn - Connection to database against which the query will be execute
        queryString - Query to be executed.
        queryAttrNames - Name of attributes whose values will be inserted as parameters into the queryString
        bindResultsToNode - If true, queryString must be a READ query and values returned by query will be added to the node as attributes
